In <strnlghtCq2z2z.Cpr@netcom.com> strnlght@netcom.com (David Sternlight) writes:

>No problem. Get a "Persona" certificate from RSADSI. It's even free. All it
>does is say that a person claiming to have the name you give them has the
>key you sent them.

...

>I know that sounds a lot like "web-of-trust" but it has the advantage that
>your key is certified by RSADSI, and thus anyone can authenticate your
>messages using the RSADSI Persona Authority public key to authenticate your
>certificate and signature. They only need that one key and not a gazillion
>for everyone who might have signed any newsgroup poster's key.

That is not what I would call a "web-of-trust", unless you consider RSADSI
trustworthy.  I do not, at this point.

